## VMSS-- virtual machine scale set (auto scaling)	
vmss automatically increase the number of vm instance has demand grow and decrease the vm instance when demand is less.

vertical scaling -- This involves upgrading or increasing the capacity of the resources of a single machine — adding more CPU cores, RAM, or faster storage
horizontal sscaling -- This adds more machines or instances to distribute the workload, often behind a load balancer. 

scale out -- adding the resources
scale in -- removing the resources

static --- public ip will not changes.
dynamic --- public ip will changes.

## manual scaling and auto scaling -- in manual scaling we define the number of instance to be created 
in auto scaling we can configure the scaling rule  for cpu by adding scale in and scale out rules.


